week 1:
- Learned the basics of Automatic Speech Recognition (ASR).
* Got acquainted with speech recognition quality metrics:
* jiwer, wer (word error rate), cer (character error rate)
* Implemented a universal pipeline for testing various ASR models, including:
* Whisper (faster-whisper), HuggingFace (Wav2Vec2), DeepGram, ElevenLabs, AssemblyAI, Speechmatics, Azure OpenAI, Google Cloud Speech-to-Text, Google Gemini.
* Integrated mlflow to track experiments:
* Raised mlflow UI using ngrok for ease of analysis.
* Conducted an analysis of the results on the first 10 examples from the dataset, compared the quality and speed of different models.#


week 2:
- Text-based Cyprus Dictionary with Greek Translation Support
 Built comprehensive bidirectional dictionary leveraging ZiartisNikolas/NMT-cypriot-dialect-to-greek model
 for accurate Cyprus ↔ Greek translations with batch processing capabilities and text normalization pipeline, train/validation/test splits (80/10/10)

- Audio-based Cyprus Dictionary with Transcribed Speech Dataset
 Created production-ready 4.4GB dataset containing 17,080+ transcribed speech segments from ±20 hours of Cyprus dialect audio, with train/validation/test splits (80/10/10)

- Fine-tuning Pipeline Infrastructure for Model Training
 Established end-to-end framework with automated data preprocessing


 week 3:
 - Trained specialized MLM BERT model based on cypriot dictionary dataset
- Researched, built and touched ASR architecture
- Ready for production ASR post-processing deployment

week 4:
- Created two global RIK datasets, separating them by train,eval,test, cleaned 15gb in total. Configured and uploaded Hellenic Greek Dataset.
- Used Scribe from elevenlabs to create transcriptions for datasets
- Finetuned lighteternal-wac2vec2-asr model and jonathas-wac2vec2-asr model on hellenic greek dataset